Security has been strengthened in and around the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) ahead of tomorrow’s national convention of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Policemen and other security agents, including operatives of the Department of State Services (DSS) from neighbouring states of Kogi, Nasarawa, Kaduna and Niger, are on the ground to complement their FCT counterparts in ensuring safety during the event. Roads leading to the Eagle Square venue of the convention and the Federal Secretariat had a heavy presence of the eyed security personnel yesterday.   2023: Ex-Senators’ Forum advises APC on hitch-free…     Consensus: APC within the law for chairmanship candidate,…     Court directs Jimoh Ibrahim to publish committal…   Also, most hotels in Abuja are fully booked by delegates and party members. The Nation gathered that governors took over many of the hotels in the Central Business Area (CBA) of the city. Five-star hotels, such as Sheraton, NICON Luxury and Transcorp Hilton, as well as Bolton White, Top Rank, Chelsea, Barcelona Valencia and Riets Continental, were full of life as delegates moved in and out discussing the convention.